headline: Nipocalimab granted U.S. FDA Priority Review for the treatment of generalized myasthenia gravis
summary: Johnson & Johnson (NYSE: JNJ) today announced the nipocalimab Biologics License Application (BLA) received Priority Review designation from the U.S Food and Drug Administration (FDA) for the treatment of antibody positive (anti-AChR, anti-MuSK, anti-LRP4) patients with generalized myasthenia gravis (gMG), as supported by findings from the Phase 3 Vivacity-MG3 study.
